        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>A lien waiver is a document in which a subcontractor, supplier, or contractor waives their right to file a mechanic's lien against a property in exchange for receiving payment. Getting lien waivers right — collecting them from every sub and supplier, tracking which are conditional vs. unconditional, and ensuring they cover the correct payment amounts — is one of the more tedious but legally important administrative tasks in construction.</p>

        <p>Manual lien waiver management via email and spreadsheets leads to missed waivers, incorrect amounts, and liability exposure. Construction software that integrates lien waiver tracking into the payment workflow reduces this risk significantly.</p>

        <h2>Types of lien waivers</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Conditional waiver on progress payment:</strong> Waives lien rights for a specific payment amount, but only becomes effective when that payment actually clears. Most common for progress payments during a project.</li>
          <li><strong>Unconditional waiver on progress payment:</strong> Waives lien rights unconditionally for a specific payment amount. More protective for the paying party — the waiver is valid regardless of whether payment clears.</li>
          <li><strong>Conditional waiver on final payment:</strong> Waives all lien rights upon receipt of final payment. Conditional on payment clearing.</li>
          <li><strong>Unconditional waiver on final payment:</strong> Full release of lien rights, unconditional. Strongest protection for GC and owner at project close.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Many states have specific statutory forms that must be used — California has some of the most detailed requirements. Always verify applicable state law.</p>

        <h2>How construction software handles lien waivers</h2>

        <h3>Procore — Comprehensive lien waiver management</h3>
        <p>Procore's commitment management module tracks lien waivers tied to subcontractor pay applications. You can require subs to submit a lien waiver before a payment is released, track waiver type and amount, and generate reports showing waiver status across all subs on a project. For large GCs managing dozens of subcontractors, this automated tracking prevents the gaps that manual spreadsheet management creates.</p>

        <h3>Buildertrend — Integrated for residential GCs</h3>
        <p>Buildertrend includes lien waiver tracking in its subcontractor management workflow. When you create a payment to a subcontractor, you can require and attach a lien waiver before finalizing the payment. The waiver document is stored in the job file. For residential GCs coordinating multiple trades on a project, this integration keeps lien waiver collection part of the normal payment process rather than a separate tracking task.</p>

